abstract: An Iowa Democrat asked him to look inside himself and reveal “a moment that you felt vulnerable.”
snippet: An Iowa Democrat asked him to look inside himself and reveal “a moment that you felt vulnerable.”
lead_paragraph: CLINTON — Every so often, Pete Buttigieg gets an out-of-left field question from an Iowa Democrat that’s not about how he’d beat President Trump or what he’d do to improve people’s health care.

abstract: Tanzania said on Saturday it had not been officially notified by the United States about a travel ban after it was targeted alongside five other countries by President Donald Trump's expanded travel restrictions on Friday.
snippet: Tanzania said on Saturday it had not been officially notified by the United States about a travel ban after it was targeted alongside five other countries by President Donald Trump's expanded travel restrictions on Friday.
lead_paragraph: DAR ES SALAAM — Tanzania said on Saturday it had not been officially notified by the United States about a travel ban after it was targeted alongside five other countries by President Donald Trump's expanded travel restrictions on Friday.
headline_main: Tanzania Says Has Not Been Officially Notified About U.S. Travel Ban
headline_print_headline: Tanzania Says Has Not Been Officially Notified About U.S. Travel Ban

abstract: With the Iowa caucuses set to kick off the primary season on Monday night, a Democratic race that began as a contest of ideas and ideologies has given way to a fixation on electability.
snippet: With the Iowa caucuses set to kick off the primary season on Monday night, a Democratic race that began as a contest of ideas and ideologies has given way to a fixation on electability.
lead_paragraph: SIOUX CITY, Iowa — After a long campaign of ideological clashes, policy debates and talk of a grand reckoning on the direction of the Democratic Party, the presidential primaries starting on Monday will be shaped by a less lofty but increasingly urgent matter: determining the best candidate to defeat an incumbent who has already proved to be a political survivor.

abstract: The U.S. Senate will conclude its impeachment trial of U.S. President Donald Trump next week, with a final vote set for Wednesday. The Republican-controlled chamber is all but certain to acquit the president.
snippet: The U.S. Senate will conclude its impeachment trial of U.S. President Donald Trump next week, with a final vote set for Wednesday. The Republican-controlled chamber is all but certain to acquit the president.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The U.S. Senate will conclude its impeachment trial of U.S. President Donald Trump next week, with a final vote set for Wednesday. The Republican-controlled chamber is all but certain to acquit the president.

abstract: U.S. senators are aiming to take final votes in the U.S. Senate impeachment trial of Donald Trump next week under a tentative deal drafted by Republican and Democratic leaders on Friday and due to be voted on later in the evening.
snippet: U.S. senators are aiming to take final votes in the U.S. Senate impeachment trial of Donald Trump next week under a tentative deal drafted by Republican and Democratic leaders on Friday and due to be voted on later in the evening.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - U.S. senators are aiming to take final votes in the U.S. Senate impeachment trial of Donald Trump next week under a tentative deal drafted by Republican and Democratic leaders on Friday and due to be voted on later in the evening.

abstract: As the slowing economy threatens Prime Minister Narendra Modi’s grip on power, the government unveiled a modest budget that one economist called “smoke and mirrors.”
snippet: As the slowing economy threatens Prime Minister Narendra Modi’s grip on power, the government unveiled a modest budget that one economist called “smoke and mirrors.”
lead_paragraph: NEW DELHI — India is stuck in its biggest economic slump in more than a decade, but Prime Minister Narendra Modi’s budget for the new year, unveiled on Saturday, offers only small steps to try to create a turnaround.

abstract: U.S. Rep. Jim Costa is something of an outlier in liberal-minded California — a centrist Democrat who supported the Keystone XL pipeline and was one of the last holdouts to line up behind President Barack Obama’s health care overhaul.
snippet: U.S. Rep. Jim Costa is something of an outlier in liberal-minded California — a centrist Democrat who supported the Keystone XL pipeline and was one of the last holdouts to line up behind President Barack Obama’s health care overhaul.
lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — U.S. Rep. Jim Costa is something of an outlier in liberal-minded California — a centrist Democrat who supported the Keystone XL pipeline and was one of the last holdouts to line up behind President Barack Obama’s health care overhaul.

abstract: The Vermont senator has made exaggerated claims or statements that lacked context about “Medicare for all,” his antiwar record and his history of bipartisanship.
snippet: The Vermont senator has made exaggerated claims or statements that lacked context about “Medicare for all,” his antiwar record and his history of bipartisanship.
lead_paragraph: Before the first votes are cast in the Democratic presidential contest, The New York Times reviewed statements Senator Bernie Sanders of Vermont has made promoting his signature “Medicare for all” proposal, highlighting his long-held opposition to military intervention and arguing that he can work across the aisle. Here’s a fact-check.

headline_main: My Culture Is Not Super Bowl Entertainment

abstract: Californians start voting Monday in a high-profile Democratic presidential primary that has no clear front-runner and could take longer to count than any previous election in a state already notorious for slow ballot counting.

lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Californians start voting Monday in a high-profile Democratic presidential primary that has no clear front-runner and could take longer to count than any previous election in a state already notorious for slow ballot counting.
